# infra/

GCP deployment configuration for `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`.

## Phase 1–2: manual deploys

```bash
# Authenticate
gcloud auth login
gcloud config set project <your-project>

# Deploy from source (one command — Cloud Run builds the container)
cd /path/to/{{PROJECT_NAME}}
gcloud run deploy {{PROJECT_NAME}} --source . \
  --region europe-west1 \
  --allow-unauthenticated \
  --min-instances 0 \
  --max-instances 1 \
  --timeout 1800 \
  --memory 1Gi \
  --cpu 1
```

`--max-instances 1` until a Cloud SQL connection pooling proxy is in place. Scaling beyond 1 without pooling will exhaust the database connection pool.

## Phase 3: GitHub Actions + Terraform

- `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` triggers on `workflow_dispatch` (manual) — flip to push-on-main once you trust the manual flow
- Terraform state in a GCS bucket; per-environment workspaces (`dev`, `prod`)
- Cloud Run, Cloud SQL, Cloud Tasks, Cloud Storage, Secret Manager, Cloud Scheduler all defined declaratively

